Happy Sweet 16th Birthday to our baby boy @liambv - Our New Year’s Day baby who brought all the joy and light into our family. This past year leading up to his big birthday was filled with all the good times as always with this son of ours 🥹❤️

Our sweet old boy Samson crossed over the rainbow bridge to where he can use his legs fully to run free in the woods last night. He lived a good full life of 13.5 years, and the last 3 years were a gift of borrowed time that we believe Louis brought to him. Samson was our serendipity dog. After our oldest daughter saved all her money she bought him for her 14th birthday. Only to realize after about a year and a half that she truly didn’t have the time to give him. We had all 6 of our children living at home at the time plus a very small back yard (he was the size of a miniature horse! Aka huge) So we adopted him out to another family who we ended up having a wonderful relationship with. We would still see and have Samson at least once a month while they were traveling. Flash forward 5 years and he made his way fully and permanently back to us as we were having him more and more since the family that adopted him was traveling so much for their business. We had moved into our current home with a lot of yard for him to roam just a year before. It was Serendipity ✨ Samson was truly the best dog ever. He was such a talker. He loved being outdoors in the mountains more than anything. We loved this boy so much and know now that he’s roaming the mountains and chasing all the deer just like he loved. 🫶🏼 Until we meet again old boy 🐾 😢

Sourdough Blueberry & Lemon sweet rolls - refined sugar and dairy free!

Roll dough: 

2 1/4 cups Kamut flour 
1 tsp baking powder 
1 tsp French grey salt 
1/2 tsp Baking Soda 

Mix dry ingredients, then add in your wet ingredients below 

Add: 
1 cup coconut milk 
1/2 cup Kamut sourdough discard 
1/2 cup organic coconut oil (melted)
2 TBSP real organic maple syrup 

Mix well, then turn out into a floured surface and knead for 3-5 minutes sprinkling Kamut flour onto your surface as you go until it’s not super sticky anymore.

Put dough back into bowl, cover with Saran Wrap and let rise for about 4 hrs. 

Turn dough out onto well floured surface and roll out to about between 1/8 - 1/4in. thick. I like to shape it into kind of a rectangle before I start rolling to keep the shape more consistent. *Be careful not to roll it too thin. 

Spread a 1/2 cup softened coconut oil 

Mix together and spread dough with date paste. 

Date paste: 
1 cup pitted dates + 1/4 cup water. Mix in a blender until smooth 

Sprinkle with a handful of blueberries (i used organic frozen ones + the zest of 1 lemon + 2 tsps cinnamon 

Carefully roll dough up, away from you into a roll. I use thread to the gently slide under my roll to cut the roll into 12 rolls. You can also use floss, but be careful not to use mint flavored. 

Place them evenly spaced into a parchment lined cast iron pan. (Mine is an 11in pan) Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown. Since I used frozen berries I baked for about 45 mins. 

Frosting: 
4 dates 
Juice of 1/2 lemon 
1/4-1/3 cup maple syrup 
1-2 Tbsp coconut oil 
1/4 cup coconut milk 
1/2-1 tsp vanilla 

Blend together until smooth + drizzle on rolls (I don’t measure this - I just eyeball it 🤪) and ENJOY!

Make a roller with me! I call this my “Liliana” roller! Simply put 10 drops of each: Grapefruit, valor, kidpower, and stress away. And then fill the rest with coconut oil!

I use this in place of perfume, because fake fragrance isn’t good for us and it gives me a headache and we don’t like headaches!😠

I put this roller is my hair and on my wrists and my neck! Let me know if you try it! If you the need the oils you can get them in the link in my moms bio!🤭🤗

We’ve been making these nonstop around here! They’re so yummy and easy to grab on the go! More info on the blog with full recipe breakdown and recipe card you can save to your phone 🫶🏼 

Healthy Refined Sugar & GF Protein Balls

Ingredients
2 3/4 cups GF sprouted oats
1 cup peanut butter (or nut butter of your choice)
1/2 cup raw honey
1/3 cup unsweetened shredded coconut
4 tbsp hemp hearts
2 tbsp chia seeds
2 tbsp flax seed meal
3 tbsp cacao nibs
2 tsp vanilla

Directions
Break down oats by pulsing in a food processor or blender (I use my vitamix on setting 4 for about 1-2 minutes or until I can see oats are mostly broken down)
Mix all ingredients in a bowl until incorporated, then add in vanilla.
Form into 1 inch balls (recipe should make 30 balls)
Chill & store in an airtight container in refrigerator

Enjoy! xx

Sourdough Discard Pumpkin Bars sweetened with Real Maple Syrup topped with a Maple Bourbon Cream Cheese frosting🍁🎃 

Since both Liam and Liliana decided to not eat refined sugar this year and their older brother Aden doesn’t eat sugar either I’ve been adapting my recipes to make their favorite treats with maple syrup instead. This is their number one request for this time of year! 

For the Pumpkin bars you’ll need: 

2 eggs
1/2 cup butter melted 
1 1/2 cup real maple syrup
1 small 15oz can (around 2 cups) of pumpkin 
1 1/2 cups Kamut flour (I’ve used a GF 1for1 flour too) 
1 1/2 tsp baking powder 
1 tsp baking soda 
1/2 tsp salt 
2 1/2 tsp pumpkin spice 
1/2 cup sourdough discard 

Optional: 2 scoops of @just.ingredients pumpkin spice protein powder (I’ve made it with and without this and it doesn’t affect the rise at all)

Preheat oven to 325° convection or 350° standard bake. Beat eggs, add in butter, then maple syrup & pumpkin. Add in flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt & pumpkin spice. Then fold in sourdough discard. Line a cookie sheet with parchment paper and spread batter evenly. Bake for 25 minutes or until the top is golden brown. 

For the maple bourbon cream cheese frosting you’ll need: 

8oz cream cheese 
1/3 cup bourbon maple syrup (I get mine at Costco)
1 tsp vanilla 
1/4 cup heavy cream 

Beat cream cheese until soft, add in bourbon maple syrup & vanilla. Then add heavy cream and whip on high for a minute. Spread on top of pumpkin bars after they’ve cooled. 

A couple notes: 
You can sub maple syrup in the frosting if you can’t find the bourbon maple syrup. If you don’t make sourdough you won’t have discard. You can disregard it in the recipe and instead add in 1/4 cup milk & an additional 1/4 cup flour. If you have any other questions ask them below! 

Also, Let us know if you try them please 🤍

Liam wrapped up his regional Mountain Bike race season today. When he came to us in April and told us he was thinking he wanted to pivot from soccer to mt biking we were thrown for a bit of a loop. But this boy had made up his mind and jumped right in to training from there. He hadn’t raced since 8th grade and really hadn’t rode his bike much besides for fun occasionally since. 

He petitioned up in the beginning of the season to be in a race division higher than where they wanted to place him and they accepted it. After some confusion on his first race where he thought he’d be starting in place 16.. he really ended up starting in place 72. That lit a fire where he ended up gapping 63 kids to take 9th place. Even after a rough crash sprinting it out at the finish line. That was the start of what was a truly incredible race season for our boy. 

We’ve seriously loved watching him race. There’s something to say for individual vs team sports ~ the camaraderie these kids have for each other is unmatched. The way his buddies run along with him, shouting his name through a mega phone while he’s racing to keep him pumped up literally brings me to tears every time I watch it. 🥹😭 They all SHOW UP for each other and cheer everyone on, I’ve never seen anything like it, and it’s pretty damn magical. 

I’m SO PROUD of this boy for following his heart and choosing to live out his passions as he wants. He’s such a constant example to me, and everyone in our family. My favorite thing that would bring my mama heart to tears was how without fail he’d lay his head on his handle bars and pray before the start of each race. That’s just who this boy is.. and man we are so lucky that he’s ours. 

Even though his regional season is over, it was so eventful! 

From puking 4 times on the course to taking the podium in his homecoming outfit for 4th place at Snowbasin. Then an incredible 1st place finish in Mantua, to ending his season in todays race in 2nd place for Regions. Even though todays race ending wasn’t what he’d hoped for-he’s ready to let it fire him up for what’s next! 

Now it’s off to the State championships for @liambv!! He’ll start in 2nd place and he’s ready for it!! 🚵

The YUMMIEST Easy GF Lasagna

Need a weekend dinner that tastes delicious but is super easy to make for your family!? This is SO EASY and is Liam’s most favorite meal ever! Since most of us are GF we use gluten free noodles but you can easily sub for regular noodles! 

Ingredients: 
1 pound lean ground beef
1 pound ground Italian sausage 
1 teaspoon dry Italian seasoning 
1 teaspoon garlic powder
2 Costco sized 28oz jars of Rao’s (Rao’s is the only option in my book. It not only is the best sauce ever, but saves you so much time! You’ll need roughly 42oz. I use 1 1/2 Costco sized jars, which are 28 oz. each.)
16 oz Ricotta Cheese
1 egg
2-3 Tablespoon’s (go with your heart) fresh Italian Parsley chopped.
10-12 Tinkyáda Organic Brown Rice Lasagna Noodles. *do not precook 
1 1/2 cups or so shredded Mozzarella Cheese
16 oz Fresh Sliced Mozzarella 
1/2 cup grated Fresh Parmesan Cheese

Instructions
In a large pan, cook ground beef and sausage. Add in the Italian seasoning and garlic powder. Cook through until browned. Drain any excess grease. Then add in the Rao’s sauce, stir and combine then remove from heat. 

In a bowl, combine ricotta cheese, egg, fresh chopped Italian parsley. 
Assemble your Lasagna:
Preheat oven to 375° regular bake or 350° convection bake. 

To assemble, spread 1½ cups of meat sauce in the bottom of a 9×13 inch baking dish. Arrange a single layer of three noodles lengthwise as shown over meat sauce. I break the a piece off of a 4th noodle to fit in the end. 

Spread one half of the ricotta cheese mixture on top of your noodles. Then top with slices of fresh mozzarella & 1/2 cup of mozzarella cheese. Add a sprinkle of Parmesan. 

Spoon 1½ cups meat sauce over cheeses. 

Repeat layers. 

Once you get to the third layer of noodles top with the rest of your sauce THEN top with remaining fresh mozzarella, shredded mozzarella and Parmesan cheese for your top cheesy layer.

Cover with foil and bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes.

Remove foil, and bake an additional 25 minutes until the middle cheese is melted and golden. Cool for 15 minutes before slicing and serving.

Let cool for 15-20 minutes before serving

ENJOY!!!

Kona, Hawaii - The Big Island! (Pt.1) We had such a fun week! This was our second time to this island for Will & I, the first for our kids. We fell in love with this island on this trip! There’s such diversity in terrain & things you can do here. You can be at the beach then drive an hour to snow ski on the Big Island! Crazy, right! 

✨Our highlight was our night swim with the manta rays! The MOST MAGICAL experience ever, a MUST DO! We used Ocean Encounters & had such a successful experience! I found a Groupon that saved us 30%. I’d honestly pay full price to experience it again. There were 17 of us in our group so we had a boat to ourselves!
🏖️ Best Beaches: our FAVE hands down was Manua Kea. It’s smaller, has fun waves for boogie boards & feels so clean. The sand is dreamy at this beach & so are the sunsets!
🏝️ We also liked Hāpuna Beach. This was Liam’s & Aden’s favorite since the waves were bigger. It’s a busier, more public vibe compared to Manua Kea. 
🍽️ Fave Foods:
🍩 if you see the Manuela Malasada truck you MUST STOP. Get some filled with Haupia & powder sugar, or ube cheesecake filled with li-hing sugar! 
🍣Best Poke bowl was in Hilo at Poke Market. 
🍧OBISIC - for the best shaved ice ever!
🍕Nui Italian - yummy Italian at our Hotel with lots of GF options!
🥗Lava Lava Beach Club for dinner was amazing! Live music & our table was on the beach in the sand!
🍍Fruit stands near Waipeo Valley - they’re all yummy, stop & support them! 
⛰️Hikes & Waterfalls: Waipio Valley Lookout - a beautiful view down into the valley. They’ve closed going into the valley to tourists. 
Akaka Falls - Super easy paved hike to see where Jurassic Park was filmed. 
Rainbow/Wailea Falls - you can swim here, easy hike, park on the side of the road. 
🛌 We stayed at the Hilton Waikola Village which was great for families. You can snorkel with turtles in the lagoon & swim with dolphins right at the hotel!

🙌🏼Share your Faves for the Big Island below please!

We were so grateful to get to have some of our friends & their families on this trip with us! We love them like our own & it made it so much fun for all of our kids 🫶🏼🤍 We all earned this trip, thanks to @ylrecognition

Take the trip. Soak it in. THESE are the memories that keep, friends. As I’ve watched 4 of my 6 kids grow into adulthood my feelings on this have become so strong. Any time we get to spend with them together is a gift. 🥹 Kona, Hawaii was so good to us. From dreamy beaches to driving through the clouds over mountain tops - night swimming with manta rays to matching family tattoos - and everything in between. We created memories to last! 

We loved getting to have @adencleverley & his cute girlfriend @bayleerisenmay with us on this trip 🫶🏼 and we missed our other older kids who couldn’t make it.

Would love for you to share your favorite family trip you’ve taken in the comments! We want more ideas!
